RegionLength.name: Descriptor region length
RegionLength.help_text: If non-zero, specifies the length of the Descriptor region.

NumComponents.name: Number of Flash Components
NumComponents.help_text: Specifies the number of Flash components that will be installed on the target machine. Valid values are 0,1,2 - 0 causes only ME region to be built.

ComponentBaseAddr.name: Component Base Address
ComponentBaseAddr.help_text: Identifies address bits [11:4] for the Component portion of the Flash Descriptor.

RegionBaseAddr.name: Region base address
RegionBaseAddr.help_text: Identifies address bits [11:4] for the Region portion of the Flash Descriptor.

MasterBaseAddr.name: Master base address
MasterBaseAddr.help_text: Identifies address bits [11:4] for the Master portion of the Flash Descriptor.

IchStrapLength.name: Number of PCH straps
IchStrapLength.help_text: The number of PCH straps to be read. Valid values are 0 to 255.

IchBaseAddr.name: PCH straps base address
IchBaseAddr.help_text: Identifies address bits [11:4] for the PCH strap portion of the Flash Descriptor.

MchStrapLength.name: Number of CPU straps
MchStrapLength.help_text: The number of CPU straps to be read. Valid values are 0 to 255.

MchBaseAddr.name: CPU straps base address
MchBaseAddr.help_text: Identifies address bits [11:4] for the CPU strap portion of the Flash Descriptor.

RegInitBaseAddr.name: Register Init Base Address
RegInitBaseAddr.help_text: Identifies address bits [11:4] for the Register Init portion of the Flash Descriptor.

RegInitLen.name: Register Init Length
RegInitLen.help_text: 1's based number of Register Init entries. Each entry is two DWORDS.

ReadStatusFreq.name: Read ID and Read Status clock frequency
ReadStatusFreq.help_text: If more that one Flash component exists, this field must be the lowest common frequency of the different components.

WriteEraseFreq.name: Write and erase clock frequency
WriteEraseFreq.help_text: If more that one Flash component exists, this field must be the lowest common frequency of the different components.

FastReadFreq.name: Fast read clock frequency
FastReadFreq.help_text: This field is undefined if the Fast Read Support is set to false.

ChipSelect2En.name: Chip Select 2 Enable
ChipSelect2En.help_text: false: The multiplexed spi_cs2/gpio_28/mgip_07 is used as a GPIO/MGPIO. true: The multiplexed spi_cs2/gpio_28/mgip_07 pin is used as SPI chip select 2.

SpiBus2En.name: SPI Bus 2 Enable
SpiBus2En.help_text: false: There is one set of SPI clk/mosi/miso pins. true: A second set of SPI clk2/mosi2/miso2 pins are enabled.

ChipSelect1BusSelect.name: Chip Select 1 Bus Select
ChipSelect1BusSelect.help_text: false: SPI Chip Select 1 is on the first set of SPI pins. true: SPI Chip Select 1 is on the second set of SPI pins.

DensityComp1.name: Flash component 1 density
DensityComp1.help_text: This field identifies the size of the 1st Flash component.

DensityComp2.name: Flash component 2 density
DensityComp2.help_text: This field identifies the size of the 2nd Flash component.

DualOutputFastReadSupport.name: Dual Output Fast Read Support
DualOutputFastReadSupport.help_text: Enables support for dual Output Fast Read Support

IllegalInst0.name: Illegal Instruction 0
IllegalInst0.help_text: Op-code for an illegal instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

IllegalInst1.name: Illegal Instruction 1
IllegalInst1.help_text: Op-code for an illegal instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

IllegalInst2.name: Illegal Instruction 2
IllegalInst2.help_text: Op-code for an illegal instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

IllegalInst3.name: Illegal Instruction 3
IllegalInst3.help_text: Op-code for an illegal instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

FlashPartitionBndry.name: Flash Partition Boundary
FlashPartitionBndry.help_text: For Asymmetrix flash parts, this is address bits[24:12] of the boundary that logically divides the flash into two partitions. The two partitions can support different eraseable sector sizes. If 0, then there is only one partition.

LowerFlashEraseSize.name: Lower Flash Erase Size
LowerFlashEraseSize.help_text: For Asymmetric flash parts, this is the lower of the two erase sizes.

UpperFlashEraseSize.name: Upper Flash Erase Size
UpperFlashEraseSize.help_text: For Asymmetric flash parts, this is the upper of the two erase sizes.

ReadAccess.name: Read access
ReadAccess.help_text: Each bit corresponds to Regions [7:0]. If the bit is set, read access is granted.

WriteAccess.name: Write access
WriteAccess.help_text: Each bit corresponds to Regions [7:0]. If the bit is set, write access is granted.

BootBlockSize.name: BIOS Boot-Block size
BootBlockSize.help_text: This strap only applies when booting from SPI. Boot from LPC (FWH) only supports a 64KB boot block size (Invert A16) and this soft strap is a don't care. Size above 256KB are only enabled if the Server Feature Disable Fuse 5 is set to '0'.
BootBlockSize.default: 000: 64KB (Default): Invert A16 if Top Swap is enabled.

DmiReqIdDisable.name: DMI RequesterID Check Disable
DmiReqIdDisable.help_text: false: DMI RequesterID Security Checks are enabled. true: DMI RequesterID Security Checks are disabled and no Requester ID checking is done on accesses from DMI. The primary purpose of this strap is to support server environments with multiple CPU's that each have a different RequesterID that can each access the Flash.

LinkSecDisable.name: MACsec Disable
LinkSecDisable.help_text: true: MACsec is Disabled. false: MACsec is Enabled.

LanPhyPcGp12Sel.name: LAN PHY Power Control GPIO12 Select
LanPhyPcGp12Sel.help_text: Set to 0 for GP12 to be used as GPIO, or 1 for GP12 to be used in native mode as LAN_PHYPC

SMT2Freq.name: SMLink0 Frequency
SMT2Freq.help_text: The value of these bits determine the physical bus speed supported by the HW.

SMT1Freq.name: Intel ME SMBus Frequency
SMT1Freq.help_text: The value of these bits determine the physical bus speed supported by the HW.

SMT3Freq.name: SMLink1 Frequency
SMT3Freq.help_text: The value of these bits determine the physical bus speed supported by the HW.

Smt3Enable.name: SMLink1 Enable
Smt3Enable.help_text: Enables SMLink1 (SMT3). This soft strap is backed up in the RTC well.

Smt2Enable.name: SMLink0 Enable
Smt2Enable.help_text: Enables SMLink0 (SMT2). This soft strap is backed up in the RTC well.

Smt1Enable.name: Intel ME SMBus Select
Smt1Enable.help_text: Enables ME SMBus (SMT1). This bit must always be set to '1'.

Reserved14.value: Prefetching is allowed to complete prior to the flushing

Reserved14.name: Reserved
Reserved14.default: Prefetching is allowed to complete prior to the flushing

Reserved15.value: DMI posted queue will advertise 16 command and 64 data credits
Reserved15.value_list: DMI posted queue will advertise 16 command and 64 data credits,,DMI posted queue will advertise 2 command and 8 data credits
Reserved15.name: Reserved
Reserved15.default: DMI posted queue will advertise 16 command and 64 data credits

Reserved16.value: Receiver detection is bypassed if DMI Force Detect is not 00
Reserved16.value_list: Receiver detection is bypassed if DMI Force Detect is not 00,,Receiver detection is not bypassed
Reserved16.name: Reserved
Reserved16.default: Receiver detection is bypassed if DMI Force Detect is not 00

Reserved18.value: DMI Tx operates in half-swing mode

Reserved18.name: Reserved
Reserved18.default: DMI Tx operates in half-swing mode

QuadIOReadEn.help_text: This soft-strap only has effect if Quad I/O Read is discovered as

QuadOutReadEn.help_text: This soft-strap only has effect if Quad Output Read is discovered as supported via the SFDP

DualIOReadEn.name: Dual I/O Read Enable
DualIOReadEn.help_text: This soft-strap only has effect if Dual I/O Read is discovered as supported via the SFDP.

DualOutReadEn.name: Dual Output Read Enable
DualOutReadEn.help_text: This soft-strap only has effect if Dual Output Read is discovered as supported via the SFDP.

TpmOnSpi.name: TPM on SPI
TpmOnSpi.help_text: This soft-strap has no effect if TPM on SPI is fused disabled

SpiTpmClockFreq.name: SPI TPM Clock Frequency
SpiTpmClockFreq.help_text: This field identifies the frequency that should be used with the TPM on SPI.

Smt1AsdAddrEn.name: Intel ME SMBus ASD Address Enable
Smt1AsdAddrEn.help_text: true: Address is enabled. false: Address is disabled.

Smt1MctpAddrEn.name: Intel ME SMBus MCTP Address Enable
Smt1MctpAddrEn.help_text: true: Address is enabled. false: Address is disabled.

Smt1I2cAddrEn.name: Intel ME SMBus I2C Address Enable
Smt1I2cAddrEn.help_text: true: Address is enabled. false: Address is disabled.

Smt1I2cAddr.name: Intel ME SMBus I2C Address
Smt1I2cAddr.help_text: Diagnostic Service SMBus Address / SMBus Wake-up address

Smt2I2cAddrEn.name: Intel ME SMLink0 I2C Address Enable
Smt2I2cAddrEn.help_text: true: Address is enabled. false: Address is disabled.

Smt2I2cAddr.name: Intel ME SMLink0 I2C Address
Smt2I2cAddr.help_text: IPMI SMLink0 Address / SMLink0 Wake-up Address

PhyConnectivity.value_list: 00: No PHY connected,,01: PHY on SMBus (use SMT1),,10: PHY on SMLink1 (use SMT2),,11: PHY on SMLink2 (use SMT3)
PhyConnectivity.name: Intel PHY Connectivity
PhyConnectivity.help_text: Defines which SMBus/SMLink segment the PHY is connected to.

SataPort5PcieP2Mod.value_list: 00 : Statically assigned to SATA Port 5,,01 : Statically assigned to PCIe Port 2,,10 : Reserved,,11 : Assigned based on the native mode of GPIO49 pin
SataPort5PcieP2Mod.name: SATA Port 5 PCIe Port 2 Mode
SataPort5PcieP2Mod.help_text: This soft strap only has effect if it is allowed by the SATA Port 5 PCIe Port 2 Mode fuse.

GbeSmBusAddr.name: GbE MAC SMBus Address
GbeSmBusAddr.help_text: This is the Intel integrated wired MAC's SMBus address.

GbePhySmBusAddr.name: GbE PHY SMBus Address
GbePhySmBusAddr.help_text: This is the Intel PHY's SMBus address.

Smt1SubDid.name: Intel ME SMBus Subsystem Device ID

Smt1SubVid.name: Intel ME SMBus Subsystem Vendor ID

PCIePortConf1.value_list: 00: 4x1 Ports 1-4 (x1),,01: 1x2, 2x1 Port 1 (x2), Port 2 (disabled), Ports 3, 4 (x1),,10: 2x2 Port 1 (x2), Port 3 (x2), Ports 2, 4 (disabled),,11: 1x4 Port 1 (x4), Ports 2-4 (disabled)
PCIePortConf1.name: PCIe Port Configuration Soft Strap 1
PCIePortConf1.help_text: These straps set the default value of PCIe Port Configuration 1 register covering PCIe ports 1-4.

PCIePortConf2_Pch.value_list: 00: 4x1 Ports 5-8 (x1),,01: 1x2, 2x1 Port 5 (x2), Port 6 (disabled), Ports 7, 8 (x1),,10: 2x2 Port 5 (x2), Port 7 (x2), Ports 6, 8 (disabled),,11: 1x4 Port 5 (x4), Ports 6-8 (disabled)
PCIePortConf2_Pch.name: PCIe Port Configuration Soft Strap 2
PCIePortConf2_Pch.help_text: These straps set the default value of the PCI Express Port Configuration 2 register covering ports 5-8.

PCIeLaneReversal1.name: PCIe Lane Reversal 1
PCIeLaneReversal1.help_text: false: PCIe lanes 0-3 are not reversed. true: PCIe lanes 0-3 are reversed for Port 1 when configured as 1x4. Sets PCIe Port1, Device 28 Function 0, offset D8[27] register.

PCIeLaneReversal2.name: PCIe Lane Reversal 2
PCIeLaneReversal2.help_text: Sets the default value for the PCIe Port 5, Device 28 Function 4, offset D8[27] register.

DmiLaneReversal.name: DMI Lane Reversal
DmiLaneReversal.help_text: false: DMI lanes 0-3 are not reversed. true: DMI lanes 0-3 are reversed.

GbePciePortSelect.name: Intel PHY PCIe Port Select
GbePciePortSelect.help_text: Sets the default value of the PRC.GBEPCIERPSEL register which is used to determine which PCIe port to use for GbE MAC/PHY over PCI Express communication.

GbeOverPcieEn.name: Intel PHY Over PCIe Enable
GbeOverPcieEn.help_text: false: GbE MAC/PHY comm. is not enabled over PCIe. true: The port selected by GBE PCIe Port Select is used for GbE MAC/PHY over PCIe comm.

SubtractDecodeAgentEn.name: Subtractive Decode Agent Enable
SubtractDecodeAgentEn.help_text: Set this bit to 'true' if there is a PCI bridge chip connnected to the PCH, that requires subtractive decode agent. Set to 'false' if the platform has no PCI bridge chip.

SerialGPIOExpEn.name: Serial GPIO Expander Enable
SerialGPIOExpEn.help_text: 'false' : Serial GPIO Expander is disabled; 'true' : Serial GPIO Expander is enabled.

USBP2PCIeP1Mode.value: 00 : PCIe Lane 1 is statically assigned to PCI Express (or GbE)
USBP2PCIeP1Mode.value_list: 00 : PCIe Lane 1 is statically assigned to PCI Express (or GbE),,01 : PCIe Lane 1 is statically assigned to USB3 Port 2,,10 : Reserved,,11 : Assigned based on the ExpressCard USB3# select pin on GPIO71
USBP2PCIeP1Mode.name: USB3 Port 2 PCIe Port 1 Mode
USBP2PCIeP1Mode.default: 00 : PCIe Lane 1 is statically assigned to PCI Express (or GbE)

USBP3PCIeP2Mode.value: 00 : PCIe Lane 2 is statically assigned to PCI Express (or GbE)

USBP3PCIeP2Mode.name: USB3 Port 3 PCIe Port 2 Mode
USBP3PCIeP2Mode.default: 00 : PCIe Lane 2 is statically assigned to PCI Express (or GbE)

PCHHotOrSML1AlertSelect.name: PCHHOT# or SML1ALERT# Select
PCHHotOrSML1AlertSelect.help_text: This strap determines the native mode operation of GPIO74: 1 - PCHHOT#, 0 - SML1ALERT#

SataPort4PcieP1Mod.value_list: 00 : Statically assigned to SATA Port 4,,01 : Statically assigned to PCIe Port 1,,10 : Reserved,,11 : Assigned based on the native mode of GPIO16 pin
SataPort4PcieP1Mod.name: SATA Port 4 PCIe Port 1 Mode

MeMdesEn.name: ME Debug SMBus Emergency Mode Enable
MeMdesEn.help_text: Enable emergency ME Debug status writes over SMBus using the address set by ME Debug SMBus Address.

MeMdesAddr.name: ME Debug SMBus Emergency Mode Address
MeMdesAddr.help_text: SMBUS address used for ME Debug status writes.

DeepSxStates.name: Deep Sx Enable
DeepSxStates.help_text: Deep Sx refers to two low power states that are referred to Deep S4 and Deep S5.

MeDebugLanEmerMode.name: Intel ME Debug LAN Emergency Mode

Smt3GpAddrEn.help_text: true: Address is enabled. false: Address is disabled.

Smt3I2cAddrEn.name: SMLink1 I2C Target Address Enable
Smt3I2cAddrEn.help_text: true: Address is enabled. false: Address is disabled.

PCIePowerStableTimerEn.name: PCIe Power Stable Timer

RegionLength.name: BIOS region length
RegionLength.help_text: This is the size of the BIOS region in bytes. Set this to 0 to make the region length equal to the binary file length (rounded up to 4k). Extra space will be filled with 0xFF.

InputFile.name: Binary input file
InputFile.help_text: This is the BIOS image binary that will be copied into this region.

RegionLength.name: GbE LAN region length
RegionLength.help_text: This is the size of the GbE LAN region in bytes. Set this to 0 to make the region length equal to the binary file length (rounded up to 4k). Extra space will be filled with 0xFF.

InputFile.name: Binary input file
InputFile.help_text: This is the Gbe image binary that will be copied into this region.

RegionLength.name: PDR region length
RegionLength.help_text: This is the size of the PDR region in bytes. Set this to zero and specify an input file if you want to tool to determing the appropriate size for the region.

InputFile.name: Binary input file
InputFile.help_text: This is the PDR image binary that will be copied into this region.

SecInputFile.name: Additional file
SecInputFile.help_text: Additional file alligned to the begining of the region.

RegionLength.name: DER region length
RegionLength.help_text: This is the size of the DER region in bytes. When editable, adjusting this value to 0, causes that the region length is aligned to the binary file length (rounded up to 4k). Extra space is filled with 0xFF.

InputFile.name: Binary input file
InputFile.help_text: This is the PTU image binary that will be copied into this region.

InputFile.name: Binary file
InputFile.help_text: This is the path to a binary file that will be used for the partitions contents.

QstConfigurationFile.name: Intel(R) QST config file
QstConfigurationFile.help_text: This is the Intel(R) Quiet System Technology (QST) configuration binary file.

PermitFile.name: Permit file
PermitFile.help_text: Adds the permit data to the Datastore.

GLutFilePath.name: Global LUT File Path
GLutFilePath.help_text: Defines a path and name for the Global Lut file.

RemoveLocalLuts.name: Remove NFT LLUTs
RemoveLocalLuts.help_text: Indicates if LLUTs will be removed from all NFT partitions.

UpdModuleFile.name: Update Image Module
UpdModuleFile.help_text: Path to the Update Image Module.

UpdateKeyFile.name: Update Image Key File
UpdateKeyFile.help_text: Path to the key file used to sign the update image.

UpdDataExtFile.name: Update Data Ext File
UpdDataExtFile.help_text: Data file that defines the Update Data Manifest Extension.

RegionOffset.name: Region Offset
RegionOffset.help_text: The offset from the beginning of flash where the ME region will start. If 0, then ftool will determine where to put it based on the region order.

RomBypassVector.name: Rom Bypass Vector Instruction
RomBypassVector.help_text: Up to 128 bits, this field represents the instruction that is placed at the beginning of the FPT used to jump to the Rom Bypass partition.

RomBypassVector_Ich10D.name: Rom Bypass Vector Instruction
RomBypassVector_Ich10D.help_text: Up to 128 bits, this field represents the instruction that is placed at the beginning of the FPT used to jump to the Rom Bypass partition.

RegionLength.name: ME region length
RegionLength.help_text: This is the size of the ME region in bytes. Set this to 0 to make the region length equal to the binary file length (rounded up to 4k). Extra space will be filled with 0xFF.

UfaBase.name: UFA Base
UfaBase.help_text: The base address where HW compressed modules are decompressed and placed.

LaBase.name: LA Base
LaBase.help_text: The base address of the 32MB logical address space where FW is paged to.

LaBase_Ich10D.name: LA Base
LaBase_Ich10D.help_text: The base address of the 32MB logical address space where FW is paged to.

MePageSize.name: ME Page Size
MePageSize.help_text: Size in bytes of each page in memory.

MePageSize_IP_PCH0_A0.name: ME Page Size
MePageSize_IP_PCH0_A0.help_text: Size in bytes of each page in memory.

HuffBlockSize.name: Huffman Block Size
HuffBlockSize.help_text: The blocks sized to be used by the Huffman compressor.

HuffBlockSize_IP_PCH0_A0.name: Huffman Block Size
HuffBlockSize_IP_PCH0_A0.help_text: The blocks sized to be used by the Huffman compressor.

UmaSize2.name: UMA size
UmaSize2.help_text: This is the amount of the UMA memory that ME will request from BIOS.

RecoveryJumperMgpio.name: Recovery Jumper MGPIO Number
RecoveryJumperMgpio.help_text: Number of MGPIO to be used as input from Recovery Jumper.

EnableDebugEntries.name: Enable Debug SEL Entries
EnableDebugEntries.help_text: If set Degug Events will be sent if necessary.

DirectFlashUpdateEnabled.name: Direct FW Update enable
DirectFlashUpdateEnabled.help_text: true if direct flash update is enabled

AlwaysOnPowerMode.value_list: Powered in All Sx States,,Powered in S0/S1 Only
AlwaysOnPowerMode.name: ME power mode
AlwaysOnPowerMode.help_text: Defines whether ME is powered in all Sx states or in S0/S1 states only. Refer your platform hardware design.

DFFDisable.name: DFF Disabled
DFFDisable.help_text: Set true to disablee IPMI DFF messages on SMLink1

PCHThermalReading.name: PCH Thermal Reading over SMLINK1 Disabled
PCHThermalReading.help_text: Set to false to enable PCH Thermal Reading over SMLINK1

FlDscrAccessCheckEnabled.name: Flash Descriptor Access Check Enabled
FlDscrAccessCheckEnabled.help_text: Set false to disable checking of host write access rights to Flash Descriptor

FlashCycleLifetime.name: Flash Lifetime
FlashCycleLifetime.help_text: Time in years the flash should last. Setting zero disables flash wearout protection in the firmware.

FlashCycleLimit.name: Flash Erase Limit
FlashCycleLimit.help_text: This number multiplied by 1000 equals the maximum number of erase cycles the flash can perform. Setting zero disables flash wearout protection in the firmware.

TicksToAdd.name: Ticks to add
TicksToAdd.help_text: This is used for access management.

TokensToAdd.name: Tokens to add
TokensToAdd.help_text: This is used for access management.

BypassInputFile.name: Legacy ROM bypass file
BypassInputFile.help_text: This specifies the file that will be copied into the first 32k of the Flash image.

FptHeaderVer.name: FPT Header Version
FptHeaderVer.help_text: Defines the FPT header type set in the FPT header.

FptEntryType.name: FPT Entry Type
FptEntryType.help_text: Defines the FPT entry type set in the FPT header that defines the type of entries used in the FPT.

MeLayoutType.name: ME Layout Type
MeLayoutType.help_text: This setting reflects the layout type used after modifying the build settings.

VeRomBypassCap.name: VE Rom Bypass Capable
VeRomBypassCap.help_text: Indicates whether ME is able to load VE Rom Bypass.

MfsLibPath.name: MFS Library Input File
MfsLibPath.help_text: This is the path to the library file generated during the build

MfsLibKey.name: MFS Library Key Value
MfsLibKey.help_text: Value passed into the MFS Library and used as the symmetric key value during encryption of the library.

EnforceModQuotas.name: Enforce Module Quotas
EnforceModQuotas.help_text: If true, the build will fail if any module does not meet its quota length.

AliasPageSupport.name: Alias Page Support
AliasPageSupport.help_text: True: alias page support enabled; False: alias page support disabled

Name.name: Partition name
Name.help_text: This is the 4 character name of the partition.

Offset.name: Partition Offset
Offset.help_text: If non-zero, this will be the offset of the partition from the start of the FPT. If the value is unusable, an error will be generated during the build.

Length.name: Size
Length.help_text: This is the length of the partition in bytes. Set this value to 0 if you want the tool to determine the proper partition length. Extra space will be filled with 0xFF.

Owner.name: Owner
Owner.help_text: This is used for access management.

ScratchSectors.name: Scratch sectors
ScratchSectors.help_text: This is used for access management.

MaxTokens.name: Max. number of tokens
MaxTokens.help_text: This is used for access management.

TokensOnStart.name: Tokens on start
TokensOnStart.help_text: This is used for access management.

DirectAccess.name: Direct access
DirectAccess.help_text: This is used for access management.

Read.name: Read permission
Read.help_text: This is used for access management.

Write.name: Write permission
Write.help_text: This is used for access management.

Execute.name: Execute permission
Execute.help_text: This is used for access management.

InputFile.name: Binary file
InputFile.help_text: This is the path to a binary file that contains the data for this partition.

Logical.name: Logical
Logical.help_text: Set to true for logical partitions within an EFFS partition

WOPDisable.name: WOP Disable
WOPDisable.help_text: Set to true for partitions without WOP

ExclusiveBlockUse.name: Exclusive Block Use
ExclusiveBlockUse.help_text: Doesn't share flash erase blocks with another partition.

DebugBuild.name: Specifies if this is a debug build
DebugBuild.help_text: This indicates whether this is a debug or production build.

InUpdateImage.name: Include in Update Image
InUpdateImage.help_text: Flag to specify if this CODE partition should be included in the FW Update Image.

SignManifest.name: Sign manifest
SignManifest.help_text: This value indicates whether the manifest will be signed or not.

BuildManifest.name: Build new manifest
BuildManifest.help_text: This value indicates whether a new manifest will be build or the manifest will be copied from a file.

ManifestFile.name: Manifest file
ManifestFile.help_text: This is the manifest file that will used instead of the signing key.

FwSkuRegister.name: Firmware SKU
FwSkuRegister.help_text: This value represents the current firmware SKU.

SigningKey.name: Signing Key File
SigningKey.help_text: This is the path to a key file that is used for signing partition manifests.

LocalLut.name: Local LUT file
LocalLut.help_text: This is the path to a Local LUT file which will contain HW compressed modules in this partition.
